11. name.indexOf(s) -> returns the index of the given string { Here s , is the string }

For example : name.indexOf("ri") returns 1 which is the first occurence of ri in string "Prince" , -1 otherwise.

public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String name = "Prince";
        System.out.println(name.indexOf("ri"));
    }
}

Output : 1

public class Main{
    public static void main(String[] args){
        String name = "Prince";
        System.out.println(name.indexOf("k"));
